CORTÉS, HERNANDO:—Carta al rey de Tidor. May 28, 1527. A. de I.;
patronato real; leg. 6. Begins “A vos el honrado é buen Rey....” Ends “os ruego me escribais; é a S.M.”, with date and signature.
Published by Montero y Vidal, Historia general, i, appendix, pp. 555–557. See VOL. II, p. 39.

[Letter to Felipe III.] Bermuda Gulf, August 16, 1604. A. de I.;
est. 68, caj. 1, leg. 42. Begins “Jhs Señor. La paz de nuestro señor ...” Ends “su amor le pido lo aga v. magd.” (in postscript).
In the letter, which is mainly religious and ecstatic in tone, mention is made of certain letters, relations, and commissions of Luis Perez Dasmariñas, which he and his companion have in their charge.
